content:
I have the error below as I try to load the Llama models:
 
Could not load Llama model from path: models/llama-7b.ggmlv3.q4_1.bin. Received error Failed to load model from file: models/llama-7b.ggmlv3.q4_1.bin (type=value_error)

The Hugging Face website says that llama-cpp has dropped support for GGML models and turn to GGUF, so I also tried models in https://huggingface.co/TheBloke/LLaMA-7b-GGUF/tree/main. However, the problem remains the same.

Could anyone help? thanks!

When using a machine with limited RAM, errors like

Bus error
Segmentation fault

Are occurring commonly

Does anyone have any idea about how to resolve these?
Is it a mistake that the lab is due during break? It is going to be very hard to do a collaborative group lab when our teammates are traveling around the world.
